ACTION:
Temporarily bypass the suspected open by directly connecting Control Module 5’s + output conductor to Control Module 7’s + input conductor, effectively jumping over Control Module 6’s series + path while leaving all other wiring untouched. Then insert the battery with all switches ON and observe whether any downstream LEDs (modules 7–8 or load indicator/lamp) turn on. This functional test will determine whether the floating + terminal at Module 6 is causing an open circuit blocking power to the rest of the chain.
