description: Temporarily bypass the suspected open by directly connecting Control Module 5’s + output conductor to Control Module 7’s + input conductor, effectively jumping over Control Module 6’s series + path while leaving all other wiring untouched. Then insert the battery with all switches ON and observe whether any downstream LEDs (modules 7–8 or load indicator/lamp) turn on. This functional test will determine whether the floating + terminal at Module 6 is causing an open circuit blocking power to the rest of the chain., outcome='Control Output Cable (+) 5 was successfully bridged to Control Input Cable (+) 7 with a 0.01 Ω connection, and all control switches 1–8 are closed. The downstream green LEDs at Modules 7 and 8 are physically missing, but both the Internal Indicator Lamp and the Main Load lamp are lit, indicating the downstream load branch is energized.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=145.0, cost_breakdown=[('short_ports', 20.0), ('close_switch', 10.0), ('close_switch', 10.0), ('close_switch', 10.0), ('close_switch', 10.0), ('close_switch', 10.0), ('close_switch', 10.0), ('close_switch', 10.0), ('close_switch', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('open_peephole', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
